Name: agentforce1__Summary__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A summary of the process in a few lines used to find the process by users through AI search. So make this contain the items a user would search for to find the process easily

Name: agentforce1__Condition__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The value of the condition, required for decision.

Name: agentforce1__Process_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The Id of the parent process. Formatted like 'PROC_xxxx' this field is to match it all up the "ultimate" parent so to speak

Name: Name
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The name of the account (not the name of the contact)

Name: ActivityDate
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The date/time that this task or action takes place

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The subject of the task. This is a short text

Name: agentforce1__Type__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Valid values are "Process", "Decision" or "End" depending on the type of process

Name: agentforce1__Action__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The action value and or action description, whatever is availible / makes sense. It will usually be the name.

Name: agentforce1__Description__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short description of the process

Name: agentforce1__Notes__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A list of notes where you can put feedback or any errors. It could be that the flow chart is invalid, missing items, infinity loops etc. If you run into these issues put them in here.

Name: agentforce1__Start_Step_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The (external) Id that is generated for the start step. This creates the link based on the external id and is not an id in the technical sense.

Name: agentforce1__Process_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The Unique Process Id of the parent formattted like 'PROC_xxxx' or if there is a clear process Id in the flow use that one. Match it to the parent value.

Name: agentforce1__Actor_Role__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The role of the actor if you can find it, Human, Agent, System etc. Be consistent and don't overcomplicate it

Name: agentforce1__Version__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: {If you can find a version, apply the version else default the version to 1.0}

Name: agentforce1__Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The unique id of this step formatted like 'PS_xxxx' use padding with zeroes for the number that is represented by the 4x

Name: agentforce1__Actor__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: If you can find any logical actor, the actor value goes in here

Name: agentforce1__Next_Step_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Field containing the Id of the next action, only applies when the type field is "Process". There is no next step when the type is "End" or "Decision"

Name: agentforce1__Next_Step_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: the Id of the next step, required for decision. This is formatted like PS_xxxx

Name: agentforce1__Step_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The name of the parent step formatted like "SP_xxxx" to link this outcome to a step

Name: FirstName
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The first name of the contact

Name: LastName
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The last name of the contact

Name: Type
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Call, Meeting or Other are the only valid values. If you have any doubts, always make this call

Name: agentforce1__Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The Unique Process Id. If on the process you can find a clear process Id populate that here. If you cannot find any specific process Id format the process like 'PROC_xxxx' and for each process up the number. Pad the value with zeroes on the left.

Name: agentforce1__AI_Model__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The AI Model Used to extract the process. This is a system field and will be specified. Ignore this for the process extraction as it is not relevant.

Name: ShippingStreet
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The street of the account address

Name: ShippingCity
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The city of the account address

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short description of the contact. Tell in a few lines something interesting about this person and tell a little about them

Name: ShippingCountry
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The country part of the shipping address

Name: AccountNumber
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: An account number. You can make this up. Don't make it too complex and make sure if you have multiple accounts they make sense.

Name: ShippingState
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The state of the account address

Name: ShippingPostalCode
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The post code of the account address

Name: Birthdate
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The date this person was born (make sure this is between 18 and 50 years old)

Name: NumberOfEmployees
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The number of employees that work for this account

Name: Email
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Email address, create something random, but make sure that it ends in .example

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Give a few lines of what should done in the task

Name: Name
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The name of the process. If there is a clear title use this tile. If not make up a title based on the file name and or what makes sense from the entire context of the process.

Name: agentforce1__Start_Step__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: This field is a reference field that is the lookup to first step in the analysed process. This is where the process starts.

Name: ContactId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Relate this field to the appropriate contact record.

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short description of the case. You can make this a few lines or even a single line that fits in with the test data theme.

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A subject in a few words that fits the theme and matches the description field

Name: ContactId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Relate this field to the appropriate contact record.

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short description of the case. You can make this a few lines or even a single line that fits in with the test data theme.

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A subject in a few words that fits the theme and matches the description field

Name: NumberOfEmployees
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The number of employees that work for this child account

Name: AccountNumber
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: An account number. You can make this up. Don't make it too complex and make sure if you have multiple accounts they make sense.

Name: ShippingCity
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The city part of the child account address

Name: ShippingCountry
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The country part of the child account address

Name: ShippingPostalCode
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The post code part of the child account address

Name: ShippingState
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The state of the child account address

Name: ShippingStreet
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The street of the child account address

Name: Name
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The name of the child account

Name: WhatId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A lookup relationship that looks up to the appropriate account.

Name: WhatId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A lookup relationship that looks up to the appropriate account.

Name: agentforce1__Latest_Version__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c:
A lookup to the Schema_Instruction_Version__c object that is a child of this Scheme instruction.
This creates the link to the latest version, so we know what record to pickup.

Name: Name
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Set this value to "Default", no other value is allowed.

Name: agentforce1__Is_Default__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Set this value to TRUE

Name: agentforce1__Latest_Version__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A lookup to the latest version of the schema mapping

Name: Birthdate
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The birthdate, make sure this is not any lower than 02/02/1900. If its lower make this the default date

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Short description about this person

Name: Email
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The email address. Always add .example at the end as this is  a test

Name: FirstName
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The first name

Name: LastName
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The last name

Name: AccountId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A reference to the parent account. Populate with the @{refId}

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short description of what the request is

Name: Status
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The status. Set this to New if you're unsure

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The case subject

Name: AnnualRevenue
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The revenue the company makes. Make sure this does not exceed 100 million.

Name: BillingCity
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The billing city.

Name: BillingCountry
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The billing country.

Name: BillingStreet
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The billing street.

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The description of the account, in a few lines what they do

Name: agentforce1__Step__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A lookup to the parent step record. Populate with the parent refId

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short case description

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The subject for the case

Name: agentforce1__External_Id__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c:
Extract the account number that is provided by the customer and put that number in this field. An example account number looks like:
ACC-00000000

Name: ActivityDate
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The date / time the action takes place

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A description of the task, add enough detail but dont go overboard

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A short subject what the task is about

Name: Id
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Map this to the input account Id, this is an 18 character salesforce id that will be specified in the prompt

Name: ContentDocumentId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Populate this field with the Content Document File Id from the input file of the prompt template. This is the Salesforce Id and not a refId.

Name: agentforce1__Process__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: A lookup field to the parent Process__c record. Apply the refId accordingly

Name: agentforce1__Next_Step__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The is the lookup reference to the next step in the process. Populate this field with the matching refId of the next step

Name: agentforce1__Next_Step__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The is the lookup reference to the next step in the process. Populate this field with the matching refId of the next step

Name: ActivityDate
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Create the data one week from now

Name: Description
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The task should be a process review task. Put a note in here to review the newly extracted process

Name: Subject
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Fill this value with: Review Process Task + The name of the process

Name: WhatId
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: This is a lookup to the process. Populate this with the process RefId accordingly

Name: agentforce1__Reason_for_score__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Put your reasoning in here on why you gave the score for the spam analysis

Name: agentforce1__Spam_Probability_Score__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Give a spam probability score between 1 and 10. Where 10 is most likely to be spam and 1 is not likely at all

Name: agentforce1__Status__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c:
9 or 10 --> "Passed"
6 or 7 or 8 --> "Check Required"
5 or lower --> "Failed"
Use these exact values

agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: The name of the product

Name: agentforce1__Allergies__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Any (potential) allergies are listed in here split by a comma

Name: agentforce1__Confidence_Score__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Give a confidence score on how confident you are about this product containing any allergens

Name: agentforce1__Estimated_Amount_Of_Calories__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Give an estimated number of calories in a normal portion of this product. Don't waste too much time on this though. It has not to be very accurate

Name: agentforce1__Price__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Put the price in here. Prices areformatted like xx.xx. Two decimals

Name: agentforce1__Reason_for_confidence_score__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Give a detailed reason on why you gave the product confidence score

Name: agentforce1__Recipe_Idea__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Based on the items on the shopping list, create me a nice but not to difficult recipe

Name: agentforce1__Shop_Name__c
agentforce1__Purpose_Description__c: Put he name of the shop in here (if you can find it )
